<!-- Campaign event template for JCS-style message traffic - header follows RichMissionMessages USAJCS format -->

<ScrollViewer xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
  xmlns:local="clr-namespace:SeapowerUI">

	<Border HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" Width="900" TextElement.FontFamily="Courier New" TextElement.Foreground="Black" TextElement.FontSize="16" Padding="45">
		<Border.Effect>
			<DropShadowEffect />
		</Border.Effect>
		<Border.Background>
			<ImageBrush ImageSource="{Binding Assets[bkg_paper]}" Stretch="UniformToFill"/>
		</Border.Background>
		
        <StackPanel Orientation="Vertical">

		<Grid
		  xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
		  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" >
		<Grid.RowDefinitions>
			<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
		</Grid.RowDefinitions>
			<Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
				<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
				<ColumnDefinition Width="3*"/>
				<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
			</Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
			
			<TextBlock Grid.Row="0" Grid.ColumnSpan="3" Margin="0" FontFamily="Roboto Mono" FontSize="14" TextAlignment="Center" HorizontalAlignment="Center">
				DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE<LineBreak/>
				JCS MESSAGE CENTER
			</TextBlock>
			
		</Grid>

			<Grid
			  xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
			  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
			<Grid.RowDefinitions>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="10"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
				</Grid.RowDefinitions>
				<Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="10"/>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="*"/>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
				</Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="3" HorizontalAlignment="Left" FontSize="16">
					FLASH<LineBreak/>
					Z 091430Z JUL 85
				</TextBlock>

				<TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="3" FontSize="16" Text="ZYUW RUEKJCS4169 1901430"/>
				
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="FM"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="JCS WASHINGTON DC"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="TO"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="THE WHITE HOUSE WASHINGTON DC//SITROOM//"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="11" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="INFO"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="11" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="SECDEF WASHINGTON DC"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="12" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="SECSTATE WASHINGTON DC"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="13" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="DCI CIA WASHINGTON DC"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="14" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="SUBJ"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="14" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="JCS SITREP 001 - PALAWAN INVASION / STRATEGIC IMPLICATIONS"/>

				<TextBlock Grid.Row="15" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" FontSize="16" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					<LineBreak/>
					SECRET
					<LineBreak/>
					BT
					<LineBreak/>
					<LineBreak/>
					1. (S) SUMMARY: Preliminary reporting indicates Soviet forces have put a large Chinese assault force ashore on Palawan island, western Philippines. Local defenses were rapidly overwhelmed. Enemy ground elements now control the southern end of Palawan and are moving to secure facilities near Puerto Princesa.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="16" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" FontSize="16" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					2. (S) ENEMY ACTION: Soviet heavy amphibious lift and strike aircraft from Cam Ranh supported the assault and placed Chinese units ashore in strength. Follow-on echelons may include ammunition, engineers, fuel, and air defense equipment intended to stabilize a permanent lodgment.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="17" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					3. (S) MARITIME THREAT:
				</TextBlock>	
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="18" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="20,0,0,0">	
					- Coastal anti-ship missile fire has been reported against U.S. and Philippine units attempting to transit Balabac Strait.
					<LineBreak/>
					- Chinese and Soviet submarines are assessed operating in Balabac Strait and adjacent approaches.
					<LineBreak/>
					- Mine laying is assessed along critical approaches to Balabac Strait and Palawan Passage.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>	
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="19" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					4. (S) FRIENDLY / REGIONAL STATUS: Available Allied forces in the immediate area are insufficient to reverse the Palawan landing. Heavy air attacks against Malaysia and the Philippines have suppressed regional strike capacity and left no reliable local air option against the invasion force.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="21" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					5. (S) POLICY / FORCE POSTURE: Movement of Allied naval forces toward Singapore through the South China Sea is no longer judged supportable without major risk of isolation. JCS recommends immediate reconsolidation of available U.S. and Allied forces at Darwin, Australia, while maintaining support to Philippine resistance.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="23" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					6. (S) ASSESSMENT: Enemy control of Palawan greatly complicates U.S. operations in Southeast Asia, and places U.S. units entering the South China Sea at risk of being cut off. If Indonesia moves from paralysis to Soviet support, southern exits could close rapidly, trapping significant forces away from logistical support and in range of Soviet bombers from Cam Ranh. Further SITREPs to follow at 12 hour intervals.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="25" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					NATIONAL MILITARY COMMAND CENTER
					<LineBreak/>
					<LineBreak/>
					BT
					<LineBreak/>
					SECRET DECL OADR
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
			</Grid>
        </StackPanel>
    </Border>
</ScrollViewer>
